                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d85">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/1129: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-05-13T19:00:00+08:00"
                            >May 13, 1930—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 13—1:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>331. Following has been received from Nanking: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“May 12, 6 p.m. Frank Lee, Vice Minister for Foreign Affairs, has just
                            informed me orally that Chengchow, Honan, will shortly be subjected to
                            an aerial bombardment and that the National Government requests all
                            Americans to withdraw temporarily from Chengchow. <pb facs="0213"
                                n="115" xml:id="pg_115"/> He said that the National Government will
                            he responsible for damage done to American property in Chengchow. The
                            American Minister, who is returning to Nanking tomorrow morning, is
                            being informed. Hankow informed.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
